label stayinghome:
    # Code done directly by Tsilla trying to mimic Chloe, will need to be proofread

    # Music.
    play music "track 07 - noise.ogg"

    scene bg mainroom
    with fade

    nvl_narrator "The doctor diagnosed Amélie with burn-out and depression, and so she went on sick leave. I hoped two months would be enough for her to heal."

    nvl clear
    
    nvl_narrator """
      The atmosphere at home felt tense.

      Even though we shared the same waking hours for the first time in months, we couldn’t behave as though Amélie was on vacation: {w} the whole situation felt wrong.{w} She was sick, unwell, and ready to burn everything.

      Work was as demanding as always. {w} When I was not embalming corpses with formaldehyde,{w} I hid the marks of death and age that my patients bore,{w} and their wounds as well.

      Meanwhile, Amélie stayed home.
    """
    nvl clear
    nvl hide dissolve

    scene bg mainroom night
    with fade

    "On the first day, I found her still lying in bed when I came back from work. {w} She was playing a video game."
    # Amélie’s sprite : eyes sunk. Pajama.
    # Leïla’s sprite : neutral expression. Outside attire.
    sub "You’re back already? What time is it?"
    dom "Hi love. It’s half past six.{w} Sorry, I didn’t have time to make you any cocoa this morning."
    sub "…half past six? Really? How?"
    dom "…is everything okay?"
    sub "…"
    sub "I’ve been playing for hours."
    sub "…I probably should go and eat or drink something."
    dom "I’ll bring a glass of water, and we have some lasagnas left in the fridge."
    sub "…Thanks babe."


    nvl show dissolve

    nvl_narrator """
      This continued on for some days:{w} I would wake up before Amélie, and I would come home to find her hollow, depressed.{w} Hungry, those times when there was nothing in the fridge that was already prepared. {w} The place, too, was a mess:{w} she hadn’t done her share of the chores,{w} and I did not quite know how to address that.

      She seemed so…{w} frail, and I felt powerless.
    """
    nvl clear

    nvl_narrator """
      Amélie was unable to explain to me why she behaved this way,{w} and broaching the subject easily made her clam up with frustration and shame{w} - because she hated the feeling of being sick, deficient,{w} of knowing there was something wrong with her that she had no control over.

      As a result, it was sometimes hard to talk with her.

      And yet… she was so hungry for affection.
    """

    nvl clear

    nvl_narrator """
      She kept asking me to stay by her side, to cuddle with her and brush her hair{w}, and, when I did, she thanked me over and over.{w} She said that I was kind not to abandon her, and she kept apologising, panicking at the idea that I might.

      It broke my heart.

      It felt strange to receive so much love from Amélie,{w} to spend so much time with her,{w} and to know that it was precisely because she was feeling so unwell.{w} It tinged any joy I could have felt from those days with guilt,{w} and it made me fear that this wasn’t real.
    """
    nvl clear

    nvl_narrator """
      And yet… my arms clung to Amélie with such strength.{w} I didn’t want to let her go. {w} I was happy that she had come back to me,{w} and I dreamt that, after all this time, things would finally be okay.

      I could fix our relationship,{w} and I would nurse Amélie back to health.
    """

    nvl clear
    nvl_narrator """
      At first, I behaved like a mother hen:{w} I woke Amélie every morning with a cup of cocoa,{w} and I made sure that she had something to eat during the day.{w} I showered her with love and care, with kisses and caresses aplenty:{w} I reassured her that everything was okay, that she could rest,{w} forget about work,{w} forget about all her troubles and that I would take care of the chores.

      Sadly, this didn’t help Amélie feel better.

      The more I cared for her, the more she seemed to retreat unto herself.{w} She hungered for love, but she clung to me in silence.

      It took some coaxing for her to tell me what bothered her.
    """
    nvl hide dissolve
    nvl clear

    # Bedroom, the two of them really close, Amélie in pajamas, Leïla in work outfit. She smiles.
    dom "Everything is okay sweetie. I love you. You’re safe here."
    dom "I can tell that there’s something you want to tell me."
    dom "You always look away from me and bite your lip when you’re like that."
    dom "Whatever it is, I’ll be there for you. I love you, and I want us to spend the rest of our life together."
    dom "I won’t judge you."
    sub "…"
    "When I saw that Amélie tried to bring herself to talk, I brushed her hair in silence, waiting for her to be ready."
    sub "…I feel like a waste."
    sub "I should be at work. I should be able to cook for myself, to clean at home."
    sub "…you’re doing everything here, and I spend my time playing Vampire Survivors or some other game."
    sub "… you should hate me for this."
    "I hugged her tighter."
    dom "You’re ill. It’s not your fault, and it’s just temporary. You would do the same for me if you were in my place."
    sub "It’s just… I…"
    sub "I don’t want to stay in bed. I don’t want to waste away."
    sub "But I try and leave and do something and I’m overwhelmed by fear and that sense that I’m going to break and I want to throw up and cry and -"
    dom "Please, take a breath."
    dom "1, 2, 3…{w} Exhale.{w} 1, 2, 3…{w} Inhale."
    dom "I’m with you."
    sub "…I want to be useful. Not to give you more work."
    sub "…but…"
    sub "…I can’t, and this makes me feel worthless."
    dom "I’ve never thought-"
    sub "Leïla, please - I’m not saying that you think I’m worthless."
    sub "I think that I am."
    sub "There’s something broken in me."
    sub "…do you think I want to stay in bed? That I haven’t showered in days because that’s what I want?"
    sub "…I hate being like this so much it makes me want -"
    dom "…Amélie, stop."
    sub "…"
    # Sprite of Leïla : eyes closed.
    dom "…please, Amélie, go take a shower for me."
    sub "…Uh?"
    # Sprite Leïla : eyes opened
    dom "It would make me very proud of you if you got out of bed and took a shower, or a bath if you prefer, and I know that it would make you feel better as well."
    dom "It’s okay if you can’t - but… can you at least try?"
    dom "Please?"
    sub "…Yes, Miss."
    sub "Thank you… Leïla."

    nvl show dissolve
    
    nvl_narrator """
      Receiving an order overrode Amélie’s mental block.

      Once she had showered, she was finally able to smile;{w} and although her expression was bashful,{w} embarrassed that she had not managed to do it by herself,{w} I could tell that Amélie truly felt better.

      She was glad to be clean, and filled with joy knowing that I was proud of her.

      Should I have sought another way?{w} Was it wrong of me to use Amélie’s submission as a lever?

      I do not know.
    """
    nvl clear

    nvl_narrator """
      Back then, seeing how distraught she was, I saw no better solution.{w} I would have done anything for Amélie to get better,{w} and wanted nothing more than for her to finally be happy.{w} So when she kept slipping back into melancholy and aimlessness,{w} when I noticed that giving her orders was the only thing that worked…{w} I embraced it.

      I chose to become her anchor; to become her Mistress.

      It is easy, with hindsight, to claim that this is the point at which I erred.
    """
    nvl clear
    nvl_narrator """
      Now things have become what they are and that I have ruined any other relationship between us other than that of a slave and a Mistress,{w} I look back on those days and I see that, rather than nursing Amélie back to health,{w} I made her grow dependent on my orders.{w} That I did not fix, but merely enabled her.

      And yet - I felt happy.{w} I genuinely thought that I was doing a good deed.{w} Amélie kept thanking her Miss after all;{w} she was more loving than I had ever known her to be.

      So I quelled my doubts.
    """

    nvl clear
    nvl_narrator """
       I shut down the uneasiness that I felt when I noticed that Amélie kept calling me Miss outside of our scenes,{w} and I buried my fear when I thought that I was abusing my power by ordering Amélie to clean our place and cook us meals.

      More than anything, I didn’t want her to think that I was acting out of pity.

      When she told me that she was genuinely happy, I trusted her.

      It felt that, had I voiced my doubts, she would have thought that I was disgusted by her needs. That I was treating her like a victim, and not a grown woman capable of making her own choices. 
    """

    nvl clear
    nvl_narrator """
      What’s more, a full time D/s relationship meant I could finally devote myself to soft scenes{w} once I had satisfied Amélie’s harsher cravings.{w} Her preferences had after all always laid with degradation, pain and fear, and, {w} faced with only so many occasions to play together, she used to turn me down whenever I asked her to be my pet for the night.{w}

      It’s not that she disliked the idea of being my puppy or my kitty, far from it in fact!{w} But experience had taught us that, were we to choose the direction of a scene,{w} our tastes seldom aligned.
    """
    nvl clear
    nvl_narrator """
      While I wished to pamper Amélie in kisses, have her perform some tricks and toss her sugar cubes -{w} to behave as though she were my darling pet for whom I held nothing but the deepest love -{w} Amélie’s fantasies turned to more abusive scenarios:{w} she longed to be a mutt;{w} to be kept in check by fear,{w} to be kicked and ridicule,{w} and to be confused between love and fear.
    """

    show sub at right
    show dom at left
    with dissolve

    nvl clear
    nvl hide dissolve

    # Still novel mode: appearance of Amélie’s and Leïla’s sprites.
    # Amélie : nerding, stars in her eyes. Leïla: concerned.
    sub "Dogs love their master no matter what, don’t they?{w} You could punish me whenever I make too much noise, use a muzzle, maybe an electric collar."
    sub "And you could maybe insult me, because dogs can’t understand,{w} and laugh at how stupid I must be to crawl back to your side, hungry for love."
    dom "But you’re so adorable when you’re on all four - how could I possibly want to hurt you?"
    dom "Seeing you like that just makes me want to kiss you and love you and give you so much praise."
    # Amélie: wistful
    sub "...It’s just a scene, Leï. Besides… what’s fun is that the dog’s mistress loves it too. She just expresses it poorly. She’s happy to have it by her side."

    "Amélie’s urges never disappeared, but she now felt satisfied enough (or perhaps secure enough in her submission) to allow me to cherish her from time to time,"
    "or to spank her without having to pretend that I had no regard for her desires and well-being."
